27typedef struct resulttable {
28 unsigned int base;
29 unsigned int last;
30 const char ** text;
31 int set;
32 ISC_LINK(struct resulttable) link;
33} resulttable;
34
35typedef ISC_LIST(resulttable) resulttable_list_t;

179#define ISC_RESULT_RESULTSET 2
180#define ISC_RESULT_UNAVAILABLESET 3
181
182static isc_once_t once = ISC_ONCE_INIT;
183static resulttable_list_t description_tables;
184static resulttable_list_t identifier_tables;
185static isc_mutex_t lock;
186
187static isc_result_t
188register_table(resulttable_list_t *tables, unsigned int base,
189 unsigned int nresults, const char **text,
190 int set)
191{
192 resulttable *table;
193
194 REQUIRE(base % ISC_RESULTCLASS_SIZE == 0);
195 REQUIRE(nresults <= ISC_RESULTCLASS_SIZE);
196 REQUIRE(text != NULL);
197
198 /*
199 * We use malloc() here because we we want to be able to use
200 * isc_result_totext() even if there is no memory context.
201 */
202 table = malloc(sizeof(*table));
203 if (table == NULL)
204 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
205 table->base = base;
206 table->last = base + nresults - 1;
207 table->text = text;
208 table->set = set;
209 ISC_LINK_INIT(table, link);
210
211 LOCK(&lock);
212
213 ISC_LIST_APPEND(*tables, table, link);
214
215 UNLOCK(&lock);
216
217 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
218}
219
220static void
221initialize_action(void) {
222 isc_result_t result;
223
224 isc_mutex_init(&lock);
225 ISC_LIST_INIT(description_tables);
226 ISC_LIST_INIT(identifier_tables);
227
228 result = register_table(&description_tables,
229 ISC_RESULTCLASS_ISC, ISC_R_NRESULTS,
230 description, ISC_RESULT_RESULTSET);
231 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
232 UNEXPECTED_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__,
233 "register_table() failed: %u",
234 result);
235 }
236
237 result = register_table(&identifier_tables,
238 ISC_RESULTCLASS_ISC, ISC_R_NRESULTS,
239 identifier, ISC_RESULT_RESULTSET);
240 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
241 UNEXPECTED_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__,
242 "register_table() failed: %u",
243 result);
244 }
245}
246
247static void
248initialize(void) {
249 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&once, initialize_action) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
250}
251
252static const char *
253isc_result_tomany_helper(resulttable_list_t *tables, isc_result_t result) {
254 resulttable *table;
255 const char *text;
256 int index;
257
258 initialize();
259
260 LOCK(&lock);
261
262 text = NULL;
263 for (table = ISC_LIST_HEAD(*tables);
264 table != NULL;
265 table = ISC_LIST_NEXT(table, link)) {
266 if (result >= table->base && result <= table->last) {
267 index = (int)(result - table->base);
268 text = table->text[index];
269 break;
270 }
271 }
272 if (text == NULL) {
273 text = "(result code text not available)";
274 }
275
276 UNLOCK(&lock);
277
278 return (text);
279}
280
281const char *
282isc_result_totext(isc_result_t result) {
283 return (isc_result_tomany_helper(&description_tables, result));
284}
285
286const char *
287isc_result_toid(isc_result_t result) {
288 return (isc_result_tomany_helper(&identifier_tables, result));
289}
290
291isc_result_t
292isc_result_register(unsigned int base, unsigned int nresults,
293 const char **text, int set)
294{
295 initialize();
296
297 return (register_table(&description_tables, base, nresults, text,
298 set));
299}
300
301isc_result_t
302isc_result_registerids(unsigned int base, unsigned int nresults,
303 const char **ids, int set)
304{
305 initialize();
306
307 return (register_table(&identifier_tables, base, nresults, ids,
308 set));
309}
